39:53.580 --> 39:57.700
There are things you can learn from a model.

39:57.700 --> 39:59.820
But the model is not nature.

39:59.820 --> 40:01.940
The fact that you have a mathematical model

40:01.940 --> 40:06.060
does not prescribe what ought to happen in nature.

40:06.060 --> 40:07.140
And this is where we are.

40:07.140 --> 40:09.740
So when you ask, what is it that theoretical physicists do?

40:09.740 --> 40:12.780
There's a misconception that we tell you what nature is.

40:12.780 --> 40:13.500
We don't do that.

40:13.500 --> 40:14.860
We cannot do that.

40:14.860 --> 40:16.860
We build mathematical models, and here

40:16.860 --> 40:20.220
is the model that we introduced earlier, the standard model,

40:20.220 --> 40:22.500
to describe nature and to mock up nature

40:22.500 --> 40:25.980
and maybe glean some principles that nature realizes,

40:25.980 --> 40:27.860
but that is not a prescription.

40:27.860 --> 40:30.700
So there is this great painting.

40:30.700 --> 40:32.460
It says, this is not a pipe.

40:32.460 --> 40:36.140
